The bending moment gives a linear normal stress distribution:\sigma^{(M)} = \frac{M_{z}z}{I_{zz}}

Combining with normal stress due to 

extension gives the stress formula:\sigma(z) = \frac{N}{A} + \frac{M_{z}z}{I_{zz}}

